by NikkiDoodle

Crowley and Alastair are brothers who run a successful multimillion dollar cooperation that supplies in trades and deals. Mary is the most unlucky woman in the world when she comes to find out that these two who she works for aren’t exactly human.

When the brothers learn of her discovery it lands her into a situation where she would rather wish she was dead.

But of course that’s what you get working with demons.

summary: crowley kissing aziraphale, marking his neck with hickies and the angel clearing his throat and asking if crowley could, well,...
body:
crowley kissing aziraphale, marking his neck with hickies and the angel clearing his throat and asking if crowley could, well, if you wouldn’t mind, dear … place one Above the Collar … and crowley’s pupils go from | to O in a matter of seconds. can’t help it when your prim and proper, normally fussy husband asks you to mark him in a spot that’d be seen.

later, they’re at a park bench and crowley’s sitting at aziraphale’s side, lifts his hand to thumb at the mark on the angel’s neck … “should’ve given you another one,” he mutters, pauses to think for a moment. and then, drawling his words with this next bit, “… could do it now, of course.” and aziraphale has to swat his hand away and tell him to be civil – but it’s said with the tone of a man who is both exasperated and completely in love.

Crowley invented Halls Cough drops.

They say it helps you stop coughing so ppl eat them but for me personally that is an unreliable claim at worst and ok ish at best. They taste bad so the whole time ur just like ‘ew, nasteeee, but if I cough again it’s socially unacceptable in class so ehhhhhhhh’

It’s a quiet yet basically harmful bit of not - really suffering that I will credit to a guy who specializes in it.

OR: Aziraphale made them. They are an attempt at helping stop a cough and save you social embarrassment but ur also suffering silently the whole time so ehhh.

summary: “Of All The Mysteries Of The World What Would You Most Like To Know?”
title: “Of All The Mysteries Of The World What Would You Most Like To Know?”
body:
Why Mark Sheppard was fired from Supernatural.

1. It wasn’t because of pay, because actors talk about that after.
2. It wasn’t because of sexual misconduct, because TMZ would’ve been all over that like Beetlejuice on Lydia.

It must’ve been something personal and bad, because no one in the cast or crew dares speak of it, probably due to legal constraints.  And he’s not even allowed at any of the SPN conventions.

Crowley was my favorite character.  I didn’t care for what they did to him in his last two seasons, but once he was gone I left The Show forever.
